<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-1111 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Central Electricity Generating Board in the UK has indicated a requirementfor at least six and possibly eight new power stations to be in operationby the year 2000, some of them coal-fired and some of them nuclear. Requirements,apart from suitability for both load following and two shifting, includelimits on both NO/sub x/ and SO/sub x/ emissions.</TEXT></DOC>